This paper deals with fully homomorphic encryption and its application in deep learning, which falls under the categories of cryptography (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on running convolutional neural networks (CNNs) on encrypted data, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses optimization techniques and GPU implementation, which are relevant to computer systems (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
